Major version change to 2.0

Attribute now accept promise 
This means some of the syntax for fabricating nested object is changed
For example, instead of: 

{ orgId: Fabricate(â€˜orgâ€™) }

now it has to be: 

{ orgId: Fabricate(â€˜orgâ€™).then(org => org.id) }

So there is no assumption that it will take the id attribute of the fabricated object, but this is better because it makes it more concise and flexible (not all fabricated object will have id attr)

Allowing promise in the custom attribute makes composing nested object more fun!
